# Supply-chain hardening: never run dependency lifecycle scripts on install
# (mitigates registry attacks à la 2025 chalk/debug crypto-clipper & Shai-Hulud).
# Verified empirically: install + unit + drizzle-kit + build + full e2e all green
# without scripts (esbuild/sharp ship prebuilt binaries via optionalDependencies);
# the production Dockerfile has used --ignore-scripts since Phase 4.
# Trade-off: our own `prepare` (husky) is skipped too — run `npm run prepare`
# once after the first install to set up git hooks (see README quickstart).
ignore-scripts=true
